Pleural region: anterior and posterior part of the body with one line of paratergites that gradually increases to 2 lines and finally 3 lines in the middle region ( Fig. 13 A–B), and the middle row greater than the others. Posterior body region starting with 2 paratergite rows and ending in a single one. Paratergite divides in few leg-bearing segments, along the distal part of body. Stigmatopleurite and prescutellum separated only by a thin membrane (less apparent than in
N. grandis
), usually the former being wider and longer than the latter. Spiracles predominantly with elliptical shape, a few oval and rounded ( Fig. 13 A–B).
